abstract: After four seasons, USA Network’s cybersecurity thriller comes to an end. And a Christmas movie from Disney+ is available to stream.
snippet: After four seasons, USA Network’s cybersecurity thriller comes to an end. And a Christmas movie from Disney+ is available to stream.
lead_paragraph: MR. ROBOT 9 p.m. on USA Network. This month, Rami Malek earned his third Golden Globe nomination for his lead role as the tortured vigilante hacker in this cyberthriller series. Elliot (Malek) and Mr. Robot (Christian Slater) have come a long way. In last week’s episode (spoiler alert!), Elliot and Whiterose (BD Wong) shared their vision for humanity in a tense philosophical debate before the creation of a seemingly parallel universe. And, if that weren’t enough of a cliffhanger, Elliot came face to face with his hooded doppelgänger and asked the burning question: “Who are you?” Catch the reveal in this two-part series finale.

lead_paragraph: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. — Racially segregated movie theaters and whites-only water fountains disappeared decades ago after court rulings struck down the legal framework of Jim Crow America, but another element of the era just won’t die: Walt Disney’s 1946 movie “Song of the South.”

abstract: The closing passage in  President Donald Trump's impeachment-eve letter  to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi had the ring of truth to it. He was writing his thoughts for history, he said. For 100 years from now, "when people look back at this affair.”
snippet: The closing passage in  President Donald Trump's impeachment-eve letter  to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi had the ring of truth to it. He was writing his thoughts for history, he said. For 100 years from now, "when people look back at this affair.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The closing passage in President Donald Trump's impeachment-eve letter to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi had the ring of truth to it. He was writing his thoughts for history, he said. For 100 years from now, "when people look back at this affair.”
headline_main: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's Distorted Letter to Dems and History
headline_print_headline: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's Distorted Letter to Dems and History

abstract: The final Democratic debate of the year took place against the backdrop of a House vote to impeach President Trump. Here’s a recap.
snippet: The final Democratic debate of the year took place against the backdrop of a House vote to impeach President Trump. Here’s a recap.
lead_paragraph: It appears nobody consulted the Jedi Council before scheduling a Democratic debate on the same night that “Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker” opened. So if you missed it, or any of the other happenings on the 2020 campaign trail this week, we’re here to help.

abstract: Delia Owens’s debut novel has sold more than four million copies — an astonishing trajectory for any new writer, much less for a 70-year-old wildlife scientist.
snippet: Delia Owens’s debut novel has sold more than four million copies — an astonishing trajectory for any new writer, much less for a 70-year-old wildlife scientist.
lead_paragraph: In the summer of 2018, Putnam published an unusual debut novel by a retired wildlife biologist named Delia Owens. The book, which had an odd title and didn’t fit neatly into any genre, hardly seemed destined to be a blockbuster, so Putnam printed about 28,000 copies.

abstract: Democrat Cory Booker has released a list of his presidential campaign's top fundraisers that includes rocker Jon Bon Jovi, along with New Jersey politicians, CEOs and entrepreneurs.
snippet: Democrat Cory Booker has released a list of his presidential campaign's top fundraisers that includes rocker Jon Bon Jovi, along with New Jersey politicians, CEOs and entrepreneurs.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrat Cory Booker has released a list of his presidential campaign's top fundraisers that includes rocker Jon Bon Jovi, along with New Jersey politicians, CEOs and entrepreneurs.
headline_main: Jon Bon Jovi Among Cory Booker's Top Campaign Fundraisers
headline_print_headline: Jon Bon Jovi Among Cory Booker's Top Campaign Fundraisers

abstract: “No one should be made to feel uncomfortable or be discriminated against because of their natural hair,” Gov. Phil Murphy said.
snippet: “No one should be made to feel uncomfortable or be discriminated against because of their natural hair,” Gov. Phil Murphy said.
lead_paragraph: One year after a black high school wrestler in New Jersey was forced to cut his dreadlocks to participate in a match, Gov. Phil Murphy signed a law this week making it illegal to discriminate against people based on hairstyles associated with race.
